getIdentity() - Method in interface categoryBase.Category.Object
Meant to return the identity morphism on this object.  For every object A there is an arrow which is a unit of composition.  This arrow loops from the object to itself.  Being a unit of composition means that, when composed with any arrow that either starts at A or ends at A, respectively, it gives back the same arrow.  The unit arrow for object A is called identity on A.
